The paper deals with image compression and its impact on perception performance, specifically in the context of autonomous driving. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image compression, which is a popular topic in the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning theory (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of different compression methods using various metrics, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the capacity of automotive bus systems, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
